ading to nerve damage.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029136,0.066651,0.080691,0.089791,0.094983,0.098421,0.10052,0.097153,0.097122,0.090065,0.082357,0.073105],"unified_progress":[0.040137,0.060641,0.075286,0.086264,0.093423,0.097754,0.098172,0.097846,0.098749,0.094182,0.085694,0.071853]},{"section":22,"text":"The headaches could be from the mass effect of the tumor.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028995,0.064433,0.077338,0.086859,0.093127,0.098062,0.10078,0.098184,0.098183,0.091889,0.085086,0.077065],"unified_progress":[0.035575,0.057479,0.07069,0.080772,0.089699,0.095538,0.097383,0.098962,0.10171,0.098994,0.093189,0.080007]},{"section":23,"text":"Wait, but the visual field defect here is bitemporal superior quadrantopia.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035633,0.06828,0.076352,0.083275,0.088951,0.09365,0.09643,0.095953,0.098896,0.09288,0.090014,0.079687],"unified_progress":[0.04522,0.061856,0.073876,0.083393,0.091454,0.095728,0.097507,0.097746,0.099113,0.09575,0.086936,0.071421]},{"section":24,"text":"Bitemporal hemianopsia is typical for chiasm compression.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031817,0.065351,0.077258,0.088136,0.096002,0.099434,0.10286,0.098965,0.096219,0.090764,0.08224,0.070953],"unified_progress":[0.068287,0.063764,0.07835,0.086637,0.093435,0.1002,0.098252,0.096599,0.092529,0.086397,0.074307,0.061242]},{"section":25,"text":"But superior quadrant suggests maybe the tumor is extending superiorly, affecting the upper part of the visual fields?","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031088,0.073877,0.087879,0.096263,0.097549,0.10042,0.10012,0.09395,0.098553,0.083041,0.07399,0.063274],"unified_progress":[0.053762,0.074508,0.093638,0.10243,0.10753,0.10239,0.098901,0.092253,0.09039,0.073838,0.06022,0.050132]},{"section":26,"text":"Or maybe the location is slightly different.","dimension":0,