e mass effects like visual field defects.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028259,0.063598,0.077454,0.088398,0.095945,0.10046,0.10284,0.098743,0.095782,0.092707,0.081531,0.074286],"unified_progress":[0.04085,0.062236,0.078828,0.088812,0.094983,0.10164,0.099022,0.098412,0.096091,0.090754,0.080242,0.068132]},{"section":32,"text":"Putting it all together: hyperprolactinemia from a prolactinoma leading to menstrual issues and galactorrhea, and the tumor's size causing compression of the optic chiasm (leading to visual field defects) and optic atrophy from prolonged pressure.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026429,0.05817,0.070741,0.081419,0.090033,0.096358,0.10078,0.09886,0.099654,0.095135,0.091842,0.090584],"unified_progress":[0.033764,0.051912,0.066252,0.076664,0.085755,0.096032,0.09568,0.098423,0.10199,0.099424,0.10032,0.093787]},{"section":33,"text":"So the most likely diagnosis is a prolactinoma, which is a type of pituitary adenoma.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022058,0.044019,0.053671,0.062359,0.071327,0.079073,0.086613,0.091219,0.099185,0.10163,0.11472,0.17413],"unified_progress":[0.02281,0.032722,0.042302,0.051693,0.057954,0.07334,0.076759,0.092509,0.10365,0.10939,0.14454,0.19234]}]}}